

To build jdee-server:

cd ~/java
git clone https://github.com/jdee-emacs/jdee-server.git
cd jdee-server
mvn -Dmaven.test.skip=true package
# cp target/jdee-bundle-1.1-SNAPSHOT.jar.jar ~/java/jdee-bundle-1.1-SNAPSHOT.jar

;; Add in an Emacs configuraton file, something like this:
(custom-set-variables
 `(jdee-server-dir (,(expand-file-name "~/java/jdee-server/target"))))

;; Not necessary with the above
Start Emacs and enter the following commands:
M-x customize
In the search field enter jdee-server-dir
In the field next to "Jdee Server Dir:" enter the directory holding the jar from step 6 (e.g. ~/myJars)
Click the "Apply and Save" button
